3490.name: Use of insecticide-treated bed nets (% of under-5 population)
3490.description: Use of insecticide-treated bed nets refers to the percentage of children under age five who slept under an insecticide-treated bednet to prevent malaria.
3490.s_name: World Bank – WDI: Use of insecticide-treated bed nets (% of under-5 population)

source.name: World Bank – WDI: Use of insecticide-treated bed nets (% of under-5 population)
source.dataPublisherSource: UNICEF, State of the World's Children, Childinfo, and Demographic and Health Surveys.
source.additionalInfo: Statistical concept and methodology: Malaria is endemic to the poorest countries in the world, mainly in tropical and subtropical regions of Africa, Asia, and the Americas. Insecticide-treated nets, properly used and maintained, are one of the most important malaria-preventive strategies to limit human-mosquito contact.
